sentences: Robert Joseph 'Bobby' Clancy Jr (11 May 1927 – 6 September 2002) was an Irish singer and musician best known as a member of The Clancy Brothers, one of the most successful and influential Irish folk groups.
Early years ==
Aoife Clancy and Finbarr Clancy followed in their father's footsteps and now tour as Irish folk Singers.
The four brothers, Paddy, Tom, Bobby and Liam released three studio albums, Clancy Brothers Christmas, Flowers in the Valley and Welcome to Our House.
According to fans who spoke with the group over the years, but unverified in the media, he and Liam got into an argument which resulted in Bobby quitting the group.

In 1976, the Clancy Brothers disbanded for a few months.
The quartet toured part-time, performing three-month-long tours each year in March, August and November only in the United States.

The quartet released the group's first studio album in over 20 years, Older But No Wiser, in late 1995, an album title coined by Bobby's wife Moira.
